The Nameless <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uweppy.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Weppy</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(5/23/01 10:32:02 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2923.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: I need advice; blues or yellows and where at 20?</span><hr size=1> Go to Lake Rathe, and kill aviak guards, these give wonderful exp, hit very weakly, have low hp, and drop bronze weapons and some times 1.5pp in money. They give more then a blue bubble at level 20 im sure (if not very close). At level 24, you can root/dot, and 2 creeping cruds will put him in running mode, or very close. So if you med, you can end up with almost full mana after you kill him. This is definalty one of the best places i have found. It beats the exp from the aviaks in SK by a long shot, and im talking LONG. My 18 monk can solo one of these and lose about 2 bubs of health, thats how easy they are :). <br>
<br>
They have around 550hp, hit for i think 31 max, not very fast, they miss alot and single attack more then double. Theres atleast 8 in the zone, when you zone in from SK, theres an island straight out from the gnoll camp with a big shrine/temple looking thing on it. Three spawn on top of that. Then behind and to the left is another island with a single treehouse that spawns two. Two spawn at the arena zone, one in its own treehouse. I know of a single spawn that spawns on a wooden plank hanging over the edge of the water (diving board), but in not sure of the location. <br>
<br>
I wouldn't advise root kiting with your 14 dot tho, it would take way to long to kill him that way, and wouldn't be worth it. You may wanna partner with anoter druid or a fighting class until you get to 21 or 22, giving you more mana to do it alone. Keep lev and sow up and you should be fine. Just ask if you have any questions. <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.showPrevMessage?topicID=2923.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.showNextMessage?topicID=2923.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2923.topic&index=3><img src=http://www.execpc.com/~msippel/thedruidsgrove/images/addreply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.emailToFriend?topicID=2923.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.threadControl?topicID=2923.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/gfx/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2923.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovehuntingguide.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2923.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub13.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cell